  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Maintenance Technician",
  "description": "<p>The successful incumbent will be responsible for the machines and facilities at the laundry, taking care to ensure that they are maintained, serviced &amp; repaired for the efficient operation of the laundry workshop. Responsible for the supervision of maintenance, servicing and repair of all machines in laundry plant, recycle plant and boiler room.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>To ensure availability of machines for production through preventive maintenance and scheduled maintenance. Examples of machines are laundry machines, low-tension switch gears water pumps, air compressors and boiler systems and recycle plant.</li>\n  <li>To improve the machine efficiency, safety and output quality by carrying out appropriate modification for the machinery or changing some repairing and maintenance methods and procedures.</li>\n  <li>To perform maintenance and repair of machines and troubleshoot machine’s fault. To be on 24-hour stand-by to attend to emergency breakdowns.</li>\n  <li>To prolong the life span of machines or expensive parts by proper regularly preventive maintenance.</li>\n  <li>To be responsible for the safety of maintenance staff.</li>\n  <li>To supervise the contractor to compete the job safely with high quality. And make sure they comply with prison rules and regulation.</li>\n  <li>To coordinate with contractor to complete the assignment.</li>\n  <li>Maintain all workshop tools and equipment in orderly manner.</li>\n  <li>To ensure Workplace Safety &amp; Health.</li>\n  <li>To maximize production capacity, productivity and quality.</li>\n  <li>To instil the right value attitude and mind set to inmate in order to change their habit, behaviour and change their life other than just train them on the technical skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Any Other Duties</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Any other tasks or duties assigned by Manager, Facilities</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in electronics, electrical or mechanical engineering, or ITC in electronics</li>\n  <li>2-3 years of experience in similar roles and industry</li>\n  <li>ITC – 5 years of relevant experience</li>\n  <li>Boiler experience in Laundry / Linen services industry preferred.</li>\n  <li>Troubleshooting electrical, mechanical, electronic, and related problems and being able to read all the above drawings</li>\n  <li>Preferably know how to read Auto-Cad and Line Drawing</li>\n  <li>Able to work in a fast-paced and restricted work environment</li>\n  <li>Able to understand electrical and mechanical systems</li>\n  <li>Boiler License Class 1 / 2 preferred.</li>\n  <li>Work Location: Changi Prison</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
